# GitHub Linguist language statistics.
#
# Linguist treats `third_party/` as vendored and drops it from the language
# bar. Because every Rust file in this repo lives under `third_party/turbovec/`
# (the upstream MIT TurboVec crate plus LodeDB's Apache-2.0 lifecycle/GPU
# patches), the repo read as "100% Python" and the Rust engine was invisible.
#
# The vendored TurboVec core is load-bearing and partly ours (encoded-row
# delta export/import, `add_encoded`/`remove_many`, calibration fingerprinting,
# and the PyO3 bindings; see third_party/turbovec/LOCAL_PATCHES.md), so surface
# the engine *source* in the stats. Upstream tests, examples, build scripts,
# and the integration shims stay vendored so they do not pad the numbers.
#
# Note: there is no C/C++ in this repo. The Python binding is maturin/PyO3
# (pure Rust). The C++ pybind11 extensions live in the upstream research repo,
# not in this spin-out.

third_party/turbovec/turbovec/src/**           linguist-vendored=false
third_party/turbovec/turbovec-python/src/**    linguist-vendored=false
